Morgan Freeman will play Mandela in the new film by Clint Eastwood
The South Africans claim that the new Hollywood film " Invictus: the Ungeschlagene " shows the world much of the country, their fight and victories, although some critics say that the roles played by the American players.
The story speaks of sport, race relations and Nelson Mandela.
The tireless fighter against the racist apartheid regime in South African Republic and its first black president, Nelson Mandela, is in his life history of the American actor Oscar, Morgan Freeman.
Freeman said that Mandela, 91 years, asked him in the film.
Matt Damon plays an important role.
I said to him: " If I must embody, I should be able to see you.
The actor aged years who is awarded a prize for his role in the drama Milion dollar baby of boxing played the role of the leader of the movement for the abolition of slavery, which ended slave, a fictional US president, and even God in the film Evan Almighty but never someone still alive and, for many people is as important as Mandela.
The former South African statesman was jailed for 27 years for his hard work in favour of the end of apartheid in the South African Republic.
He was released in 1990 and became president of the country for four years.
In 1993 he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize.
Invictus is a Latin word meaning unbeaten and it is the title of a poem by the English author William Ernest Henley, published in 1875.
The challenge was to speak as he
The film tells the true story of the joint efforts of Nelson Mandela and the captain of the South African rugby team, Francois Pienaar, leading to the country. The new President Mandela knows that his country still divided racially and economically after apartheid.
He Believes that is able to unite his people through sport and decides to unite the rugby players, who are among the outsiders in the world.
The South African team fails to reach the World Cup in 1995.
Freeman worked for several years to bring the history of Mandela on the cinema screens.
He had no other goal than to play this role to bring the these as closely as possible to the reality, said Freeman.
The biggest challenge was, of course, so to speak like him.
The actor said that if he and the world political were in the same area, he would have tried to meet with Mandela, dinner with him, to be behind the scenes before his speech.
The most important thing was for him to shake Mandela's hand.
I realized that when I shake hands, I recover your energy, it is transmitted and I had the feeling of how you feel, he said.
It is important for me to try to become a different person.
Matt Damon plays in the film François Pienaar, the captain of the national rugby team, in which there is a majority of white players.
The actor said that he had six months to prepare for a role in the harsh world of rugby.
It was a big surprise For him, when finally met For the first time with Pienaar at home.
I remember when I come to the door of the house, he opened and the first thing I said to Francois Pienaar in my life was: ' in the film much higher ".
Despite the obvious differences between the characters of the players and their real models, under the leadership of the director Eastwood received positive opinion and there is even talk of ambitions for the Oscars.
The film critic of the Daily Variety, Todd McCarthy summed up his assessment in these words: " This was a very good story, a film very well done. "
In the film on the website rottentomatoes. com, Invictus received 76 percent of positive assessments.
The secret of the splendour on Norway resolved: the Russians have tested a missile
Norway was a ray of effect of unknown origin.
The Russian Ministry of Defence has recognized that yesterday was tested near the Norwegian border an intercontinental ballistic missile.
The launch has been a failure and the type " Bulava " which was originally to be the pride of the Russian army is becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
His presence repeated in the test of the missile has not had the desired effect on the success of the test flights.
Bulavá, in Most cases, it was not flying or there was damaged in the air.
In Russian newspapers speak of " Bulava " as " a missile that did not fly. "
A missile that flies, but do not
This 13th test took place at the beginning.
Only at the end of the flight that there was further damage to the apparatus.
This is clearly the engine of the third stage of the rocket that exploded.
This time, " Bulava " was launched from the nuclear submarine Dmitry Donskoy, which plunged sailing under the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missile launched from a boat that is moving and
That is why It is likely that the mysterious light caused by an unspecified fliegendes object on Northern ways the damaged " Bulava. "
The Norwegians have also since the first moment not doubt that it is a Russian rocket.
The generals argue that this time, we cannot talk of failure.
The first two stages of the rocket and the breakdown occurred in the third.
In the previous cases were damaged the engines in the first stage.
Although none of the test launches went smoothly, the direction of the Ministry of Defence only six out of thirteen have been failures.
The success rate of almost 50 per cent full of optimism to the generals and they claim that one day " Bulava " fly without problems and even will take up to ten nuclear, whose total weight of 1.15 tonnes.
The legendary Fetisov has signed the 51 years an annual contract with CSKA Moscow
The legendary defender Viatcheslav Fetissov will return in a professional match in 51 years.
The former world champion, Olympic champion and holder of the Stanley Cup will help his team of CSKA Moscow in need and will play on Friday in the mourning Khl against St. Petersburg.
Fetisov, who ended his career with forty years in 1998, is currently the President of the CSKA.
After the injury of Denis Kuliash we urgently need another defender.
Fetisov has regularly coached and agreed to help the team.
We just have to solve some formal affairs, quoted the agency AP's coach of the club Sergey Nyemtchinov, of Moscow.
It is not yet clear whether the return of the famous player will refer to a single party.
I think that Fetisov is one of those who are able to lift the mood of the other players, said Nyemtchinov.
According to AP, in the case of his return to the ice, Fetissov becomes the oldest Russian professional hockey player.
In the NHL, the legendary striker Gordie Howe played an entire season for Hartford and scored 15 goals and 26 assists.
The oldest of the famous five, Fetisov, Kasatonov - Makarov, Larionov, Krutov, is one of the best and most successful hockey players in history.
In the colours of the Soviet Union won two Olympic Games, seven world championships, triumphed in the Canada Cup and World junior Championship.
In the second part of his career, he also in the NHL, where he twice in the Detroit won the Stanley Cup.
Since 2001 he has been a member of the hockey Hall of Fame.
Hyundai has listened to the unions and cancels all overtime
The direction of the car factory in Nošovice agreed with the unions to cancel all overtime.
It is precisely because of the frequent extra work, the unions have declared a state of emergency strike on Monday.
The spokesman confirmed the car factory Hyundai, Petr Vanek.
The management, however, wants for this year to agree with the unions on a Saturday.
We cannot abandon our production plan, it is essential, that is why We proposed voluntary overtime on Saturday, 19 December, knowing that there would be two teams, said Vaněk.
The site Sedmička. cz indicated that the company has offered a bonus of 400 CZK employees who would be part of the team on Saturday.
The bonus will be paid for the last Saturday, 28 November.
According to The company decided to change the way to motivate its employees in exchange for overtime.
Either they receive the supplement for hours, or they can take a replacement leave on 28 December and extend the Christmas Vanek.
In addition, all employees of the sessions on Saturday will receive compensation for the costs of transport and for their lunch.
Given the fact that the extra work was the most urgent and the warmest in the comments and complaints of trade unionists and last week, the production has the management yesterday afternoon decided to cancel all overtime for the month of December, said.
The staff of the car factory were forced to work Until last week, practically every day two hours in addition to their eight hours.
The unions after signing of the agreement will revoke the emergence of strike.
The following negotiations between the management of the car factory and trade unionists must take place on Friday afternoon.
The union leader Petr Kuchař said on Wednesday that if they are to meet the demands of some and can sign a joint document that they are prepared to lift the strike.
The situation in the car factory has deteriorated last week, on Wednesday, when approximately 400 employees spontaneously went on strike because of overtime.
They also protested against the poor conditions of payment and the alleged harassment.
The direction that employees had to work overtime to meet the requirements and supplement cars.
Trade unionists in his declaration of the strike on Monday, the unions have also demanded that the employees who ceased production are not subject to any sanctions.
The unions are asking the company to reduce the time spent in overtime to a minimum.
In addition, they want this year for this work remuneration of 5,000 kroner.
The car factory Hyundai Nošovice currently employs 2,000 people.
In the series production was launched last year in November.
It has produced approximately 80,000 vehicles until September of this year, with a production capacity of 200,000 cars per year.
Czech discovery: a substance that operates on the HIV virus
The team of Czech and German scientists test new combinations that can slow the spread of HIV in the body.
The main advantage of the improved substance is that it is also on the viruses that are resistant to drugs.
In some cases This is more important than the fact that the compound is not as effective in a common variant of the virus, as well as some drugs already available.
The disease AIDS can be cured until now.
However, It can prolong the lives of patients through a mixture of drugs that prevent the replication of the HIV virus in the body.
However, their use has a series of side effects.
If the replication of the virus were also has the development of so - called resistant viruses on which the medicines are no longer effective.
The work of the experts of three institutes of the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic, the Všcht Prague and the University of Heidelberg opens the way the resistance of the virus.
They have shown that the substances called metalocarboranes act on the protein responsible for the spread of the HIV virus.
The metalocarboranes are an assembly of boron, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt.
These compounds block the spread of the virus in a different way of all drugs used today, and so that is why they could overcome the problem of resistance.
In The work of researchers to discover new substances " improved ", on the basis of their knowledge of the molecular mechanism of the virus.
The metalocarboranes have a single three - dimensional structure: two cages poliedros composed of atoms of boron and hydrogen and carbon are united by a metal atom, in this case the cobalt.
A virus traitor and resilient
The HIV protease is a protein of the HIV virus, which is essential to the life cycle of the virus.
Without the proteasis of HIV, there is caused by the fragmentation of the HIV virus and not create mature and infectious particles of the virus.
If we stop the HIV protease, stop the spread of the virus in the body of the patient, the scientists in a press report published by the Institute of organic chemistry and biochemistry of the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic.
In an article published in the scientific journal Journal of Medicinal Chemistry, scientists describe a series of combinations in which two pairs of cages (see table) are united by a short organic link, which is then systematically amended.
A little weaker, but more reliable.
The evidence of The effect of this series of substances on the HIV protease was tested in test tubes and its variants resistant, obtained from patients with HIV.
The effect of the Metalokarborane in the common variant of the enzyme is not as strong as on the clinically used medicines, but they do not lose their effect on the Resistentvarianten, against which the medicines are often ineffective.
The metalocarboranes, with their unique mechanism of action and their other properties as their biological and chemical stability, low toxicity and the possibility of other chemical changes are therefore interesting combinations to consider more towards the development of effective drugs against HIV, says Pavlína Řezáčová, head of the laboratory of structural biology of the Institute of organic chemistry and biochemistry and molecular genetics Institute of the Academy of Sciences.
