The vaccine will be free and voluntary
The vaccine neumococal from January will put an end to the usual habits.
It will be the first to be free and at the same time voluntary.
The already, saying that a compulsory vaccination would be more effective.
The preparations for the introduction of the free vaccination against neumococos.
The drug Institute is already the highest prices of vaccines, which will pay for health insurance.
The experts also clear in the process of vaccination.
The new vaccination
Free vaccines for children born in August.
Since January, children born last year from 2 August can be vaccinated against pneumococcal free.
The condition is that they have not yet been vaccinated.
Those who began with the vaccine last year or earlier, you have to cover other doses of the vaccine.
The first dose of the vaccine must be received between the third and the fifth month of the child.
Last year, a quarter of families left voluntarily vaccinate their children against.
The parents paid DKK 1600 and more for a dose.
The vaccination of younger requires four doses.
Experts estimate that each year the health insurance spend 300 to 450 000 kroons in doses of vaccine.
They save but the treatment, which is needed for children are not vaccinated.
Until now, the state spent by the vaccination of children around 500 000 annually.
The vaccination repaid was introduced with the so - called Janota package.
The neumococo is the cause of otitis media, but also of serious infections including meningitis and blood poisoning.
According to surveys in hospitals, until 28 deaths of children under 10 years caused by pneumococcal infections.
Apart from the Czech Republic, approximately 40 other countries have introduced vaccination repaid.
The vaccine will be mandatory?
At the same time, said that this vaccine duty could be in the future.
From January, it must be covered by insurance companies and voluntary.
The compulsory vaccination would be better, For example, the head of the civic association Nahlas.
His association has long promoted the pneumococcal vaccination.
The experts At an international conference, in which our association participated, were not very satisfied with the fact that we have voluntary vaccination.
This is not ideal.
On the other hand, we are pleased to achieve at least this.
I believe that this is the path that we must now follow said Kalovský.
But the Ministry of Health does not want to change the procedure of vaccination against.
At the moment I do not think at all, said his spokesman Vlastimil Sršeň.
The voluntary vaccination has its disadvantages, say doctors.
The Hana Cabrnochová, president of the Society of paediatricians, acknowledges that a voluntary vaccine has its drawbacks.
If all children were vaccinated, it could consider a reduction of renewals of vaccinations " in the situation where the vaccine is such a sum I understand the decision making voluntary vaccination, " said Cabrnochová.
The experts expect that from next year, more than 80 percent of young parents will vaccinate their babies.
The Vaccination against Pneumokokken is a big change also because as the first vaccination in children which is funded by the health insurance and not the state.
The insurance companies should spend the money for the prevention, so that they save for further treatment, explains Cabrnochová.
Doctors have to buy the vaccine for themselves.
This is a concern of the practical paediatricians, the purchase of vaccines.
Previously, The vaccines had to be bought by insurance companies and distributed to doctors, the same way as when the state gives them other vaccines.
Some Members were, however, that the insurance companies, " take the money from the health insurance. "
The doctors will have to buy the products and wait until the insurance companies pay them.
According to the estimates, pediatricians individually will invest in vaccines 40 000 per month, which is a significant sum.
It will not be easy, said Cabrnochová.
