In April, its applications have increased to more than 1,800 GBP per month.
The interest rate on the loan RBS of Mr Duncan has not been changed at that time, suggesting that all the increases were intended to finance the loan of £75,000.
The standard variable mortgage interest rate fell from 7.94 percent in December 2007 to 4 percent in March this year, the rate that is now.
