" In fact, it is now national, you have to live on budget " and you are treated as "
He said: " I have spent my money in my garden and I ask a tiny part, based on what is appropriate.
And I could ask for much more, but I do not. "
The Member, a millionaire from his former career as an oil trader, was questioned in the first place on their spending in May, when it emerged that he had claimed thousands of pounds for his garden before agreeing with the fees office that could be considered excessive ".
An activist has dug a hole in the form of the symbol of the pound sterling in the lawn of Mr Duncan in protest, after it was revealed that he had requested 4,000 pounds for three years.
Last night, when asked about the increase of the mortgage, Mr Duncan said: " It was for improvements, adopted both by the office of salaries and subsequently by Legg. "
He added: " There is no problem of evasion or development or use of rules or whatever.
This is completely within the limits, in the rules, authorised, etc.
This could not be clearer or more simple. "
