The Mexican government plane arrived on Wednesday in El Salvador to restore Mr Zelaya, returned to their place of origin, according to a source of the Directorate General of Migration.
The coup government wanted to force m. Zelaya to " resign " and to request political asylum abroad.
But the president refused, because he wanted to go to Mexico as head of state invited.
The coup government " has suffered a new defeat by asking me to give up my office (...) , they wanted to resign, " said Zelaya on Thursday to radio Globo, which tends since the beginning of the political crisis that has lasted five months in the Central American country.
I can stay here ten years, I have my guitar, added by playing a few agreements the deposed president, refuge in the Brazilian embassy in Tegucigalpa for two and a half months.
The Embassy of Mexico has presented us with a request, but unfortunately we could not accept it request for asylum, said on Wednesday the Minister of the Interior of the coup government, Oscar Raul Matute, the Honduran radio HRN.
I ask asylum to any country, responded Manuel Zelaya in an interview with the channel Telesur, whose headquarters in Caracas.
A possible departure of Honduras will do as president of the Honduran people, he said.
The Rumours about the departure of Zelaya had mobilised on Wednesday the supporters of the deposed president, who gathered around the Embassy of Brazil, besieged by the military.
The Brazilian Foreign Minister Celso Amorim, criticised the position of the coup government.
