Zelaya, who had moved closer to the socialist President Hugo Chavez, was ousted on June 28, the day organized a referendum to prepare for his re - election, against the advice of the Supreme Court, the army and the Congress.
From his exile in Costa Rica, he returned by surprise on 21 September and took refuge in the Brazilian embassy.
If it is, he will be arrested for the crime of " high treason justice, according to the coup government.
The de facto President Roberto Micheletti has managed to organise a presidential election on 29 November to replace Mr Zelaya.
Porfirio Lobo was elected during the controversial ballot recognized by the United States but disputed by Latin American countries such as Venezuela, Argentina and Brazil.
Three days later, the Congress voted overwhelmingly against the return of Mr Zelaya to power until the end of his mandate on 27 January.
