Managerial revolution or end of the intelligence?
If nothing changes in the management of the major French companies, our fight for the development of economic intelligence have been in vain ...
For more than a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies in relation to its employees, recalls the position of the company vis à vis consumers before the marketing: it is to join the staff to " values " determined from above as it was made at the consumer products designed by the technicians of the plant.
By putting the customer at the heart of the company, the marketing revolution gave the strategies of conquest of the markets place ... although the authoritarian temptation to impose products separately factors preferences of customers regularly again!
A demobilisation of employees can lead to a deadly demoralisation.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of the iceberg of a much more general phenomenon that affects in particular the executives.
This demobilization seriously undermines the development of all intellectual functions of the company, including R& D and, even more importantly, the economic intelligence.
Indeed, the business intelligence) " demands that all the parties involved (...) a proactive approach and a forward - looking vision "; it needs by employees a commitment that is completely opposed to the recommendations of an authoritarian direction.
That is why we are calling for a managerial revolution, which would put the staff at the centre of the concerns of the company as the customer.
The usefulness of internal polls
The internal opinion polls, as the questionnaire submitted by Orange to its salariés - will encourage the managerial revolution in practice?
Unfortunately, I fear not.
- in principle, because I could see that, faced with a new situation, and after many detours, to do ... what it has always done.
- Secondly, because the authoritarianism - one of the pathologies of the power in proportion to the importance of its own failures.
- Finally, because most of the leaders have a simplistic view of human behavior.
From the large schools of engineers, they have a mechanistic interpretation of psychology.
They adopt, by intellectual comfort, the old theory, reactivated recently by the " neuroscience " American and widely disseminated, institutes and the media behind their backs.
Thus, suggesting that it is possible to handle the " levers " (sic) of the commitment of executives, a recent survey by Ipsos published in Le Figaro. fr reaffirms the managers in a position of management, unsuited to today's world.
Identify and measure the factors of mobilisation
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern companies, is taking a vision of human behavior.
It is to integrate, in any reasoning or practice of governance, a fundamental fact: for employees, the commitment to the company is only possible if it is clearly as a means to a portion of their dreams, their ambitions and their projects.
Currently, only the studies from the analysis motifonctionnelle adopt this concept of the motivations of employees.
These studies have shown that they believe their companies based on a predetermined which allows them, through their image of the company, to assess what it offers them to achieve their life projects.
Thanks to the identification and the measurement of these factors of mobilization, business leaders can monitor, predict and anticipate their " social performance " and invest its human resource management " in the place. "
They create a fertile ground for the harmonious development of a robust and effective economic intelligence.
