The big American banks, very affected by the crisis, their state shackles.
The Bank of America announced Wednesday that it had fully repaid to the Treasury $45 billion (more than 30 billion euros) in one fell swoop.
And also the group Citi plans to repay state aid, according to a report by the United States.
