More than a footnote on Herta Müller
In Germany and is nice almost no control ... " is the first line of a poem by Werner Söllner in fragments of language, in which tematiza experiences of arrival in Germany a dissident, who won the freedom, but has lost both his language area.
Werner Söllner, born in 1951 in Banat in Romania, was first professor of German and English in Bucharest and later as director of collection in a children's book publishing, before moving to Frankfurt am Main.
Söllner is with various literary prizes, in 1993 kept the legendary Frankfurter Poetikvorlesungen the Goethe University, and since 2002 he has director of the forum of literature in Hesse in the Mousonturm in Frankfurt.
Given that speak quite last Tuesday during a meeting in Munich, the " German literature in Romania in the mirror and the distorting mirror of your Securitate files. "
Visibly unsafe and ashamed, Söllner read out a statement in which he admitted to his fellow writers such as Richard Wagner William Totok, Franz Hodjak, and Helmuth Frauendorfer for the Securitate.
Together with some of those present in 1989, Söllner had received the prize of the German language.
The trials began in 1971.
I am, Söllner, " someone who has not sufficiently stood auxessais attempts to provocation of fear of the Securitate. "
The poet Werner Söllner is IM Walter.
Almost simultaneously with the honoration Nobel Prize for Herta Müller and his literary copies with the mechanisms of power of the dictatorship, the literary scene is shaken and in particular the community of German authors from Romania, and the evil of a political system in a case that makes based on police surveillance and espionage.
Werner Söllner is, so far after bisherigem knowledge can say, not only the perpetrators, but also a victim.
In his Securitate file Im Walter had played a role, said the specialist literature Michael Markel after the confession of Söllner and it refers to the positive influence of the Walter for him.
He had It in for him at the time sensitive points " herausgehauen, according to Markel.
" I feel the moral need to make this comment.
The form in which Söllner made his statement and before the public was unexpected, the confession of a former dissidents and its cooperation with the Romanian secret service, however, is not so surprising.
Germany was a cosy reserve for spies of the Securitate had already written Herta Müller in July in the weekly " Die Zeit, having read his own record of 914 pages.
Those involved have surely speculation and will know in some cases, what names were hidden behind Sorin, Voicu and the pseudonyms of Walter.
Unlike the review of the Stasi files with a controlled procedure in Germany, the dealing with the legacy of the Securitate files is still very confused.
A systematic clarification was boycotted and hampered in recent years.
A National Council for the clarification of the files of the Securitate (CNSAS) was created in 1999, corresponding to the launch of the acts since then, however, is more slowly.
Since 2005, there is a law that regulates the administration of the acts.
The influence of former members of the Securitate in Romania is still Nobel Prize for literature to Herta Müller, very high, is confirmed by an interview with a former head of the Securitate of Temesvar after the announcement of the award of about the Prize winner.
" She had a psychosis, and in the end only once.
The infamy of power, said quite openly in the form of freedom of expression.
Of course, inevitable questions arise with the case Söllner, as so often when there is blame.
Why only now? who was harmed? The calm reaction of the listeners off the confession of Söllner leaves hope that the continuation of this chapter will be defined more by the desire for knowledge and not so much of blame and shame.
On the genesis of the work of Herta Müller, who received the Nobel Prize yesterday, it is more than a footnote.
