The World championship heavyweights
Ardent in Bern: Kevin Johnson the challenger constantly verbally and gestuellement the world champion Vitali Klitschko with words and gestures.
But after twelve rounds difficult the Ukrainian defended his title of heavyweight in the version of the WBC.
The trial of the judges was unanimous.
Hamburg - Vitaly Klitschko remains world champion of heavyweight.
The champion of 38 years in the version of the night Association of WBC defeated in the of Saturday in Bern the American Kevin Johnson by unanimous decision by points (120: 10) .
For Klitschko it was the third successful defence of the title since his return in October 2008.
Previously, the Ukrainian had already twice world champion of associations WBO and WBC.
Unfortunately, it was not possible to make the noqueo KB.
Klitschko his record to 39 victories in 41 professional fights, twice had to be overcome because of injuries.
The challenger Johnson had to accept the first defeat in his fight number 24.
In the Berne before 17,000 spectators In the arena wanted to dictate the Klitschko, with a height of 2.02 metres, the fight with his left hand.
But Johnson, 11 centimetres smaller, before the duel, announced the end of the era Klitschko, was again and again the blows of the world champion, so that Klitschko could not crucial to the goal.
Overall, the passive Johnson too little for a challenger, has tried to move the rounds.
Although he provoked Klitschko with words and gestures, its blows only rarely reached the world champion.
Still, he is now the second boxer after Timo Hoffman in the year 2000, have exceeded with Klitschko distance of twelve rounds.
The challenger had made a lot of noise in the Swiss capital before the fight.
He offended Klitschko as " ugly zombie ", the " is not really capable ".
The weight, the champion was left on Friday to Johnson the sun glasses of the nose " in order to be able to see his eyes. "
Fourth victory since the comeback of Klitschko.
Klitschko remained in his fourth fight after his Come back on 11 October 2008
After a break of almost four years, he had beaten at the time the Nigerian Samuel Peter in Berlin and recovered " their " of the WBC belt, which he had previously had to surrender without a fight.
This year, defending his title of champion, he won the fight against Juan Carlos Gomez of Cuba and in September against Chris Arreola, of the United States.
" I only have a blow in this fight, and I am in perfect form, " said Klitschko to explain his rapid return to the ring.
But His dream is still collect all four major titles in His family.
His brother Vladimir is world champion of associations WBO and IBF.
However, the belt of the WBA But the Briton David Haye - after this in November the 2.13 meter Nikolai Walujew.
In the summer, Haye had cancelled a fight against Vitali Klitschko planned for September.
Supposedly is planning its promotion society now the fight against Klitschko to play this game at Wembley Stadium in London.
The case Kunduz
Frontal attack from the opposition: the head of the group of the Greens, Jürgen Trittin, accused the Minister of Defence Guttenberg of lying in the case of false information on the Case Kunduz.
The SPD and the Left demand explanation to the Chancellor.
Hamburg/Berlin - following the most recent revelations about the air attack in Kunduz, the opposition has criticized the Defence Minister Karl - Theodor zu Guttenberg (CSU) , have cheated with knowledge of the facts.
The Minister said the deadly bombing of two on Saturday, transmitted by the television channel ARD, the head of the Group of the Greens, Jürgen Trittin, said in the news programme ".
This means that he lied.
The order to kill was in breach of the rules of the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan (ISAF) .
This is the essence of the report that had the NATO, and that has been read by Mr Guttenberg, Trittin said.
On Friday, it was revealed that the attack was not just to destroy the trucks kidnapped, but also to kill two Taliban leaders.
In the air attack According to investigation report of NATO, 142 people had been killed or injured was launched at the request of the German Colonel Klein, military commander of Kunduz.
The Greens, the SPD and the left on Saturday called for Chancellor Angela Merkel (CDU) , immediately before the Bundestag and also to clarify what Guttenberg really knew about the incident.
Mrs Merkel must clarify whether a strategy of targeted killing part of the federal government's Afghanistan policy of the and if the Chancery, the army and intelligence service have approved this new strategy, Jürgen Trittin and the colleague from the Greens Renate Künast.
The government spokesman Ulrich Wilhelm rejected the criticism.
The chancellor did not exert any influence on concrete actions of the German army in Afghanistan, he said.
On Saturday, also had transcended misgivings about the presentation by the Ministry on the reasons for the dismissal of the Inspector General Wolfgang Schneiderhan and Secretary of State Peter Wichert.
According to the information from the Spiegel, both had reported to correct and completely against the backdrop of the attack on the convoys.
Officially, it was said that they would have denied the existence of the reports of NATO and the Minister sensitive details.
Of the two top officials has, However, that they had informed the Ministry of Defence of the existence of several reports, including a two - page document of Colonel Klein and a report of the military police.
Wichert should have asked in a letter to clarify the facts, the newspaper " Frankfurter Allgemeiner ".
So far it has not received a response, it says.
The ministry said on Saturday, not to the accusations and pointed out that will be in the Committee of inquiry of the Bundestag, which formed next Wednesday.
Dream worlds
Some people see, awake, images and hear voices that others do not see or hear.
Not only in the case of the mentally ill or under the influence of drugs, the boundaries between fantasy and reality.
As long as these phenomena occur during sleep, everything is in order.
When we are lying in our dark rooms, we can do without hindrance to the wildest fantasies.
However, awake, experienced the dream, hear and see things that others do not see or in the Western world to be crazy or drugged, or at least to be an original.
But such images and voices arise not only in the mentally ill or under the influence of drugs.
The blame our imagination: the same neural processes that enable us to design houses, paint pictures or write novels, but that the boundaries between the dream, madness and reality.
The states of consciousness A in the form of a dream, in the most diverse forms, in the best case we call them visions, and at worst madness.
But even if the trigger and the effect differ, the visions of the mystical Hildegard von Bingen, the experiences of the prophet of the new Age Carlos Castaneda, the psychosis and hallucinations similar processes.
Hallucinations or delusions, if the balance of the neural messenger substances of communication in the brain - especially the dopamine, serotonin and noradrenaline is disrupted and the interaction between different parts of the same.
Complex hallucinations and wahnhafte thoughts are very often during a schizophrenic psychosis.
The gravity has no power over him
The relationship between madness and dream has occupied philosophers and doctors Since ancient times.
Aristotle realised hallucinations as a form of the dream in the state, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of the modern psychiatry, found in 1861, a " great similarity between the madness and the to Sigmund Freud the dream was " a psychosis, with all the absurdities, composed ".
It is the autumn of 2001, when Henning T. transformed into a character.
His body is in two dimensions to the colours.
The gravity has no power over him, is floating near the ceiling.
He feels a kick.
Behind him, figures of demons with wings, with red as blood, showing teeth.
They are pursuing, with heavy boots and flameantes, cast against the walls, he feels the pain throughout the body.
Voices the walls and radio.
It can no longer bear them, the voices that insult and offend.
Henning T. snaps two cables from the stereo, knotet attached to form a noose and a hook attached to the ceiling.
It is rising on a loudspeaker and sets the noose around the neck.
The.
The rope was.
What you will serve as a lesson, the voices in a chorus to extract the eardrums, " sees the clinic and do you cure! "
Today Henning T. 40 years, he lived six acute psychosis, the last 2 years ago, the first in nearly 20 years.
It was triggered by LSD.
His diagnosis is schizoaffektive paranoid psychosis, moreover, it is, he takes medication, against The depression, mania, schizophrenia.
He has learned to live with his illness, he is married for three years.
In the psychosis I have experienced the most terrible worst fear and deepest despair, he says.
The illusions are a cruel reality
About one percent of the population suffers at least once in a life of schizophrenia; in psychiatric clinics is the most common illness after the depression.
In a crisis of schizophrenia, people can no longer tell the difference between the inside and the outside world, they are in a state of anxiety that can lead to hallucinations, delusions of grandeur, megalomania, relational or persecution.
Particularly widespread is the hearing voices: voices that give orders, command, or dialogue.
The optical hallucinations are not rare.
The person can no longer able to distinguish what is trivial, the brain can the important and no longer filter the disturbing signals, awareness is awash with impressions.
As the dream, the psychosis opens the floodgates to a torrent of ideas and fantasies that come from the deeper layers of conscience.
The perception of reality in the psychosis is focused on the subject, says Professor Thomas fox, head of the Department of Psychiatry in the Universitätsklinikum Heidelberg.
The schizophrenic is in the centre of the situation, everything has a meaning focused on him.
At the same time it is found in a passive role, as in a dream, overwhelmed by events and cannot act on them actively.
That is why the schizophrenic often feel threatened, controlled and manipulated.
In general it is not possible to adjust the reality to them, the illusions are a cruel reality, wake up is excluded.
Having experienced a once in the life of a hallucination.
Unlike in the dream, says fox, " the sensory and spatial structure of reality that is perceived in the psychosis, basically. "
The thoughts and hallucinations are based on reality, the alienation of the experience takes place in a real framework.
Why does exactly our brains antics, researchers are still a puzzle.
Exceptional conditions can bring everyone to lose the perception of reality, according to Fuchs.
But only a small number of people develop a psychosis.
There seems to be a genetic predisposition to schizophrenia, but studies on twins have shown that genes are not the only determinants.
Researchers assume that those affected suffer brain damage.
We suspect that the neuronal maturation of the brain is disrupted at an early stage of development, for example by a viral infection of the mother during pregnancy, explained fox.
But it remains unclear how this alteration of the neural system, which occurs and the fact that it is not for many years.
Environmental factors also play a role - stress or a traumatic experience can be a trigger of psychosis, if there is a predisposition.
Similarly, the hallucinogenic drugs can trigger psychosis, because they interfere with the neurotransmitters.
When our brains.
This is crazy, Psychotiker suffer from their hallucinations and says professor of psychology Erich Kasten of Lübeck is that the order to get rid of them, while others pay for drugs that allow them to obtain.
The perception pleasant or unpleasant illusions is often just a question of The point of view.
Kasten collects for ten years reports of hallucinations and visions and has analysed the results in the book his the unreal world in our head published last year.
The hallucinations are among the typical symptoms of psychosis, but also an impressive number of many other diseases.
These include mental disorders, such as borderline or depression but also epilepsy, multiple sclerosis, Alzheimer's disease diseases such as migraine, and head injuries.
It is surprising that in certain conditions even the brains of healthy people is subject to hallucinations.
The hallucinations, according to Kasten, composed of fragments of memories that normally are inhibited.
They Arise when the areas of the brain that process sensory perceptions are hyperactives or are little; when our brains hot, but also when there is a lack of stimulation.
The drugs can trigger this state in The same way that the brain damage or a psychosis.
But also the lack of stimulus, stress, the evil of love or other mental states.
In recent studies have been up to a third of those polled said that at least once in the life of a hallucinations.
In the summer of 2005, Sarah K. 16 years, she lives in a small town in Mecklenburg - Western Pomerania and it goes to the school.
A normal girl.
If it were not for the images and voices.
During the break, it can happen that a schlaksiger boy with long, dark hair and runs the floor.
When she replied his comrades, surprised - no one else sees or hears this boy.
They believe that the timid girl is a ensoñadora a little strange, but Sarah K. not dreaming, it is certain.
It is awake, hear and see the boy as she sees and hears the girl who is sitting next to her on the bench.
They can feel his presence even, at least a few moments.
It is a pleasant feeling, like the boy.
Am I crazy? , asks them sometimes.
But she knows that this young and the other visions are not real and they will disappear again.
At night, the appearances are alarming.
The visions are often a burden.
When it is in class sometimes it can follow the course because the professor in their eyes and ears is presenting a new colleague, while for the rest it is invisible to others and that the mathematical equations.
At night, the appearances are alarming.
While waiting in the dark room to reach the dream, which is far too little and too late, they often cannot distinguish whether she is awake or dreaming, if the images we see, the faces grimaçants or the girl with arms and legs, with the bleeding before their eyes open or closed.
Let me in peace, they are the characters.
Parents and friends told them nothing, which would be crazy.
Autumn 2009. Sarah K. is now 20 years old.
Approved last year selectivity and lives with her boyfriend.
A year ago the hallucinations have stopped.
Since it came into contact via the Internet with the psychologist Kasten, she knows that she is not crazy.
The madness is also a work of art of despair.
When a person is socially isolated or suffers a restriction of incentives, it is very likely that after a certain time.
I assume that the brain is not enough, that there is animation.
Sarah K., daughter, had little fear of other children and often played alone.
Their hallucinations began when, with 13 years, learned that the man she called Daddy since it was in age, was not his biological father.
As visual and acoustic hallucinations the same brain areas are active in the the real impressions and noise, it is affected as Sarah K. difficult to distinguish between vision and reality. " experience, " says place in the brain, the reality is formed from there.
The hallucinations are also images that form in the brain, which is why they seem so real. "
For Kasten, dreams are also a form of hallucination.
The hallucinations of healthy people do not differ fundamentally from those of an acute psychosis.
Unlike the schizophrenic, mentally healthy people are able to recognize their views as unrealistic.
That is why Kasten advises his patients to cherish the hallucinations as a special talent.
Border state between dream and hallucinations
In our world too focused on the much bewusstseinszentrierten imaginary experience often, generally patologizarse, says Michael Schmidt - degenhard, professor in Heidelberg and chief of the clinic and psychotherapy of Florence Nightingale hospital in Düsseldorf.
A psychosis is a serious disease, painful but which also contains something positive, creator - the madness is a work of art of despair.
Schmidt - degenhard has investigated the so - called oneirismo, a particular form of form of awareness, which is perceived as if it were a dream.
The experienced oniroïdes are very complex semi - dimensional, detailed and that the person who are seen as real by the lives and that it cannot differentiate the dream even when it is awake.
The state of consciousness oniroïde occurs during a trauma or in extreme situations of illness, as for example in patients with polyradiculopathie fully aware, experiencing a motor paralysis.
According to Schmidt - Degenhard, when a person is threatened by a loss of self and the world, due to a total and permanent inability to move, it replaces the real situation its own imaginary world, the reality is, says that by
A kind of border state between dream and hallucinations.
As it is not possible to overcome the situation in reality, a change in the world, but the real situation is represented in the imagination.
An intensive form of to give meaning and interpretation to an intolerable situation in itself that our own ability allows us not to sink into nothing of the loss of consciousness.
Everything is real, even later in the memory
Also The art historian Peter Cornelius Classen, describes his experiences in his book " change of heart " as a rescue action of the soul.
He is 49 years, when his conscience embarked on trips of several days after the operation of a heart valves with a heart transplant included, while his body was sentenced to immobility in the intensive care.
Claussen are in a world created by the same and visited places foreign travel in time. It old man in bed, in a sanatorium rail, a robot for his health.
He lives in the early Middle Ages of nobles who drugs from blood.
He was abducted by a Greek on the motorcycle in his home country, surfing with his hospital bed in the Alps and meeting a Korean mafia.
It absorbs completely in this imaginary world, everything is real, even later in the memories.
These internal travel For Claussen fundamentally different from any dream.
Dream is a different state, he describes his experience.
On the contrary, the memories from mental travel are extremely clear and very detailed even years later.
They are much more distinct and more intensive than the real experiences.
The intensity of this experience the horizon of the rest of our other everyday experiences, according to the psychiatrist Schmidt - degenhard.
Ultimately, the oniroïdes, psychosis, hallucinations and drugs show how fragile our internal figures of external reality in the even when we are awake.
Any change in the state of consciousness, summarizes the psychologist Kasten, " can lead to a distortion of what we call reality. "
An experience which might also be enriching.
