75% of working mothers have had problems because of their maternity
The Discrimination in the work has increased in recent years, especially for women of the younger generations who want to be mothers.
It reveals the study " fertility and professional career women in Spain ', produced by the CSIC in collaboration with the Institute of women.
The survey conducted on 9 737 women aged 15 to 75 years leaves no doubt about it: 75% of working mothers saw their career opportunities in the workplace because of motherhood.
The study indicates that there are many differences in the beginning of life in a couple and the number of children, depending on whether or not the women work and the type of work.
Those who do not work outside the home, working part - time work or have a stable, starting before couple, have their first pregnancy earlier and have more children.
By contrast, women with stable employment, mainly in the public sector, delaying the coexistence and maternity, and have fewer offspring.
" Women between 35 and 49 years with a fixed work have their first child, on average, 3.7 years after being only the drawing, a figure that rises to 4.1 women with fixed jobs have needed more time to achieve them, which has led them to postpone the union and the arrival of children.
In addition, the type of work exerts great influence on motherhood, although less about the timing of the pairing, " explains the researcher of the CSIC Margarita Delgado.
The level of education is another factor that widening the gap in the age of marriage for women and to have the first child.
According to the survey, the higher the level of education, the more they marry and have their first child.
The difference is also among women of the same generation.
For example, in the group between 35 and 49 years, those who have elementary and higher were respectively mothers for the first time to 25.1 and 32.1 years on average.
" There is, depending on their level of education, another difference between the women.
While those with elementary school, marry and have their first child before finding stable employment, those of average levels or higher invest this sequence and give priority to obtaining a stable work as a precondition to marriage and the arrival of a child, " said Delgado.
