Cowardly aggression
Last week, my mother, who was about 70 years of age was walking by our neighbourhood in the municipality of Fuenlabrada when a group of young people between 15 and 18 years spent with her and our dog, a sang - mélé, rescued the perrera and with no more than six kilos, and without saying a word, they hit him two kicked that left the dog seriously injured.
Our outrage is great because we do not find the fun in a gratuitous attack to a small and defenceless animal, which of course, was on a leash.
Add to this the indignation of a woman who was walking quietly and that, when these individuals came to fear for their physical integrity, as a attack an animal is capable of doing the same thing to a woman, a child, an old man or, weaker than him.
The incident occurred at 5 p. m. on a Tuesday as another in a normally quiet.
The dog was crying all day.
Of course, we have filed a complaint in a nearby police station that we doubt that serve much and not to touch the sensitivities, we just want to clarify that the cowardly killers were Spaniards.
The outrage has led us to denounce this fact.
We do not understand what is happening among young people to consider fun free of charge to a defenceless animal that we love, companionship and friendship.
We do not know where the good education and respect for animals and people.
Michelin and Fesvial together for the use of the Helms
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, in collaboration with the Spanish Foundation for road safety (Fesvial) , has launched a campaign to promote the use of helmets, mainly among the younger motorcyclists, reported today the two structures.
This initiative seeks to raise awareness of the importance of the helmet, since it is the only element of protection to prevent injuries to the head, or even death in the event of an accident in two wheels.
Michelin indicated that this campaign is part of his commitment to road safety, which " goes beyond the design and manufacture of products always safer " and said that it also contributes to this objective by other actions to educational and informative.
This new campaign to promote the use of helmets in the motorcycle, under the slogan " to be or not to be ', will have a first phase posters will be distributed in more than 500 motorcycle workshops, in order to ensure the widest possible dissemination.
Finally, Michelin stressed that road safety " is a constant concern " for the company, because as a manufacturer of tyres for two - wheeled vehicles, one of its main purposes is to develop products always safer.
The sale of light commercial
After Almost two years, the market for light commercial vehicles is beginning to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9,425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of declines, according to figures from the manufacturers ' association Anfac and sellers Ganvam.
However the good news, since the reference for comparison, the month of November 2008, was particularly bad, with a decrease of 60% on the previous year.
However, despite the surge in the last month, the accumulated during the 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
Since January, 95.853 units have been sold together all vehicles that make up the category of light commercial vehicles (derived from passenger cars, pick up, vans, pickup trucks, vans and light trucks/chassis.
Furthermore, have not gone away the clouds that most affect their demand, although they are also purchased by individuals, most of the purchases are made by small and medium - sized enterprises, which pay in almost 100% of cases through external funding.
Thus, in addition to the restrictions implied by the limitation of bank loans, other factors such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the poor economic situation.
Faced with this situation and unlike the passenger cars, aid for the purchase of the 2000E.
In addition to individuals, the self - employed and SMEs wishing to acquire a light commercial vehicles of up to 3.5 tonnes with a level of CO2 emissions than 160 grams per kilometre, but the number of operations speaks for itself.
Yesterday, in Ganvam reminded the need for the administration to devote special attention to these vehicles and also to the industrial vehicles (trucks and buses) .
The dealers association of predicts a similar to the year 2010, for which estimates a fall in sales (for passenger cars and 4x4s) of 19%.
The emergency brake is now mandatory
As happened with the anti - lock brakes ABS and as will happen with the ESP stability control systems on the emergency will have to be a compulsory element in European cars.
In fact, They are already in all passenger cars and light commercial vehicles newly registered, while the rest is set for a waiting period until the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to strengthen the protection of pedestrians, even if, by its mode of action, it can also help prevent many rear shocks.
The assistant to the emergency brake is increasing the pressure on the brakes in the event of an emergency, the system detects by the driver.
But it does not always maintained the pressure until the end.
According to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for car Bosch, a third of the drivers involved in an accident had not come to step on the brakes before the collision, and half of them had not the full force.
Up to 1,100 accidents
The intervention of the aid, revancha, requires the braking system, reducing the distance that used the car to stop.
According to a study by the EU itself, if all cars were equipped with this type of elements, up to 1,100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be avoided each year.
This reduction would be even more important with greater - it is estimated that the popularization of so - called intelligent emergency braking with damage to people - once the would be avoided.
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system that (through a radar or a camera) detects obstacles and warns the driver, in addition to act slightly on the brakes.
If the driver reacts, helps to increase the pressure on the pedal, if necessary.
If it does not react, and although the collision is inevitable, the device is the maximum effort on the brakes in order to minimize the damage.
