Users of Facebook can know the salary they deserve according to their profile, thanks to a new application of Trovit, the search engine with the largest number of real estate, employment and vehicles in Spain.
The tool " How much should be paid? " calculates the salaries of users from more than 140 000 job available Trovit in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where must introduce their profession, years of experience, age and the city where you want to work.
In the week that the application has been in operation, the search engine has found that in general, the Spanish worker " feels badly paid, " said in a press release the responsible for the product of Trovit, Albert Ribera.
According to the data available Trovità from its search engines in the United Kingdom and France, the Spanish are the worst paid.
A British computer programmer 45,226 euros annual gross and one French, 31,059, while a Spanish receives 24 000.
In the same way, a driver takes 34.247 euros annual net in England, 25 751 in France and in Spain.
According to Trovit, the worst paid work in Spain is the waiter, with annual net 11,592 euros; followed by the seller, with 14 725 euros and the worker, with 15,667 euros.
